steps:

  1. open your internet broweser
  2. go to start and hit run
  3. type cmd
    4 when the black thing pops up type in ipconfig/all
  4. it’ll show your ips
  5. look for one that says 192.168 blah blah ect ro w\ ur original ip is.
  6. look at what end number is

Your server should now let players on ect ect[/quote]Are you saying everyone here who needs to portforward are kids?

item.title: Portforwarding problem
item.dc:creator: @xX_Energy_xX xX_Energy_xX
item.description:
@xX_Energy_xX wrote:

ok heres a guide
steps:

  1. open your internet broweser
  2. go to start and hit run
  3. type cmd
    4 when the black thing pops up type in ipconfig/all
  4. it’ll show your ips
  5. look for one that says 192.168 blah blah ect ro w\ ur original ip is.
  6. look at what end number is
  7. go back to internet browser and type the ip
  8. type in the password for ur network (might need ur parents to tell u it)
  9. go to advanced settings
  10. change the last number on the port to the last number on your ip

Your server should now let players on ect ect
